Cenchrus pennisetiformis

    Authority   H.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4393

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A tufted grass reaching up to 60 cm in height. USES
   Used for pasture and withstands heavy grazing. It can be used for
   stream bank protection in rivers and creeks. GROWING PERIOD
   Summer-growing perennial grass. COMMON NAMES White buffel grass,
   Cloncurry buffel grass, Slender buffel grass. FURTHER INF White buffel
   grass can be found between latitudes 10°N and 20°S from the
   Mediterranean region to the hotter and drier parts of India, Myanmar,
   Sri Lanka and northeast Africa. In Queensland, it can be grown at
   elevations between sea level and 300 m. It is very persistant,
   withstands droughts well, will survive seasonal floodings and recovers
   well after fire.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Skerman P 1990 pp 275-278 [TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, DRA, TEXT, FER, LIG]
   Bogdan A 1977 pp 74 [USE]

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
